SYSTEM SOFTWARE:
---------------
MDMGR is now in the form of a Terminate and Stay Resident program.
The MD DATA system software is installed by including the following
lines in autoexec.bat:

    c:\mddata\mdmgr.exe
    c:\mddata\mdfsex.exe

The SETUP utility includes these lines automatically unless instructed
otherwise. 

NOTE: this installation may not match printed instructions.


REINSTALLATION:
--------------
When reinstalling MD DATA software, use the existing MD DATA directory
as the target directory and overwrite the existing files. Failure to
use the existing directory will result in multiple copies of
MDmgr.exe and MDfsex.exe in the autoexec.bat. There will also be
two paths to MD DATA software with the earliest installation having
precedence.

If MD DATA is reinstalled to a separate directory, the autoexec.bat
must be edited manually.


WINDOWS INSTALLATION:
--------------------
If Windows is started from the autoexec.bat, MDmgr.exe and MDfsex.exe must
be moved above WIN.com or MD DATA will not be available for Windows. The
lines must be moved manually.


EXCUSE LIST:
-----------
This release includes the following caveats:

  - does not support hybrid MD DATA discs
  - does not support multiple character sets
  - does not support booting
  - MDfsck is not supported under Microsoft Windows
  - When starting up the computer, the MD DATA file system with default
    settings occuipes part of the conventional memory.  Therefore, there
    will be less free conventional memory left that may cause inabilty to
    run other applications.  To avoid this situation, omit unneccesary
    device drivers or use UMB to gain free conventional memory.  (Adjust
    the set up according to memory related instructions of DOS/WINDOWS
    manuals.)  Even there is still a lot of memory or system resources
    left when running mdformat on Windows, the error message "\unable to
    access mdctl" may come up, and this can be caused by the same reason 
    (not enough free conventional memory) as above.
  - The number of directories allowed on MD DATA is regulated depending on
    file access speed.  Total number of directorys which can be created on
    an MD DATA is approximately 500.  If "Unable to create directory" for
    DOS or "-Create Diractry- Make sure the disk is not full or 
    write-protected" for Windows message appears while the data is being
    copied to MD DATA, please select "OK".  In such case, please use
    commercilly available file compression tools to decrese the number of
    directorys and files before saving data on MDDATA.

