Portable MD DATA drive (MDH-10) Manual Correction
-------------------------------------------------
There are corrections to be made on the page of "Troubleshooting".  
On the page of "Message while installing the software for DOS" (page 42), 

for Message: NO MD DATA devices foundthere is Solution: Install the SCSI!
software correctly. There are several causes and solutions to this message, 
so please erase the above solution and add the following to the manual.  

  Cause 1    : The power/mode switch is set to [Audio] mode and the
               host computer cannot recognize the MD DATA drive.  
  Solution 1 : Select [DATA] mode on the power/mode switch and restart
               the system.

  Cause 2    : The SCSI cable is not connected properly and
               the host computer cannot communicate with the MD DATA drive.
  Solution 2 : Connect the SCSI cable correctly.

  Cause 3    : SCSI ID conflict.
  Solution 3 : Set different SCSI ID numbers for each peripheral device.

  Cause 4    : The ASPI manager does not support the SCSI host adapter or
               the SCSI card. 
  Solution 4 : Install a correct ASPI manager for the supported SCSI
               host adapter / SCSI card.

Portable MD DATA drive (MDH-10) Manual Correction END
